'''Kataoka Shrine''' (かたおかじんじゃ) is a {{ill|lt=Shinto shrine|Q845945|WD=Q845945|1=Shinto shrine}} located in {{ill|lt=Yoshida Town|Q1202789|WD=Q1202789|1=Yoshida, Shizuoka}}, {{ill|lt=Haibara District|Q1203336|WD=Q1203336|1=Haibara District, Shizuoka}}, {{ill|lt=Shizuoka Prefecture|Q131320|WD=Q131320|1=Shizuoka Prefecture}}. Its former {{ill|lt=shrine rank|Q10444029|WD=Q10444029|1=Shakaku}} was that of a {{ill|lt=Modern system of ranked Shinto shrines#Village shrines|Q712534|WD=Q712534|lt=village shrine|1=Modern system of ranked Shinto shrines}}.

=== Enshrined deities ===
* {{ill|lt=Sumiyoshi Sanjin|Q1114013|WD=Q1114013|lt=Sokotsutsuo-no-Mikoto, Nakatsutsuo-no-Mikoto, Uwatsutsuo-no-Mikoto|1=Sumiyoshi sanjin}}
* {{ill|lt=Empress Jingū|Q232803|WD=Q232803|lt=Okinagatarashihime-no-Mikoto|1=Empress Jingū}}

=== Overview ===
According to shrine tradition, it is an ancient shrine that was invited from {{ill|lt=Yamato Province|Q907495|WD=Q907495|1=Yamato Province}}’s {{ill|lt=Kataoka Shrine (Ōji, Nara)|Q43594918|WD=Q43594918|lt=Kataoka Shrine|1=Kataoka Shrine (Oji Town)}}, and it is listed as a {{ill|lt=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|Q11064932|WD=Q11064932|lt=Shikinaisha|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō}}.

During the reign of {{ill|lt=Emperor Nintoku|Q313119|WD=Q313119|1=Emperor Nintoku}}, a divided spirit was invited from {{ill|lt=Sumiyoshi Taisha|Q705949|WD=Q705949|1=Sumiyoshi-taisha}} in {{ill|lt=Settsu Province|Q864163|WD=Q864163|1=Settsu Province}}, after which it came to be known as Sumiyoshi Daimyōjin (Sumiyoshi Shrine). Following the {{ill|lt=Meiji Restoration|Q8707|WD=Q8707|1=Meiji Restoration}}, Kataoka Shrine was adopted as the official shrine name.

Within the shrine grounds, the boat-shaped object “Sumiyoshi-maru” is displayed.

=== History ===
The date of foundation is unknown. Records indicate that the shrine buildings were rebuilt in the 4th year of {{ill|lt=Shōhō|Q1146192|WD=Q1146192|1=Shōhō}} ({{ill|lt=1647|Q6935|WD=Q6935|1=1647}}).

In {{ill|lt=1913|Q2080|WD=Q2080|1=1913}} (the 2nd year of {{ill|lt=Taishō|Q329174|WD=Q329174|1=Taishō era}}), the shrine buildings were renovated from thatched roofing to tiled roofing, based on designs by {{ill|lt=Heisaemon Itō|Q16766564|WD=Q16766564|1=Heisaemon Itō}}, an {{ill|lt=Imperial Household Artist|Q11481067|WD=Q11481067|1=Imperial Household Artist}}.

After the war, the heiden (offering hall) was constructed<ref>{{Cite web|Japanese
  |author = Kataoka Shrine
  |url = http://homepage2.nifty.com/sugao/
  |title = Kataoka Shrine (History and Shrine Tradition)
  |accessdate = 2016-07-31 }}</ref>.

=== Auxiliary shrines ===
The auxiliary and related shrines within the precincts are as follows.

'''Shrines within the grounds'''
* Funatama Shrine
* Hoshinomiya Shrine
* Tsushima Shrine, Inari Shrine, Itsukushima Shrine
* Jūnishin Shrine, Nishinomiya Shrine, Kotohira Shrine

